interactions.lmstext: 1. Blood leaving the right atrium passes through the _________ ________ valve.
2. The right side of the heart pumps blood into the _____________ circulation.
3. The superficial cardiac plexus is located between the ________  ________ and the ________ __________.
4. Ventricular systole causes the semilunar valves to ___________ (open/close).
5. The second heart sound, dub, occurs at the beginning of ventricular ____________ (systole or diastole).
6. The cardiac plexus receives parasympathetic fibres from the ________ nerve.
7. The first heart sound, lub, is caused by the closure of the ___________ valves (atrioventricular or semilunar).
8. Place the structures comprising the conducting system of the heart in the correct order.
9. Blood leaving the left ventricle passes through the ________ _______ valve.
10. Blood leaving the left atrium passes through the ________ _______ valve.
11. The first heart sound, lub, occurs at the beginning of ____________ (systole or diastole).
12. Blood leaving the right ventricle passes through the ________ _______ valve.
13. The deep cardiac plexus is located between the ________  ________ and the ________ __________.
14. Sympathetic preganglionic neurons innervating the heart are located in spinal levels T___ to T___. (two numbers separated by one space)
15. Ventricular systole causes the atrioventricular valves to ________ (open/close).
16. Ventricular systole causes the semilunar valves to ___________ (open/close).
17. The left side of the heart pumps blood into the _____________ circulation.
18. Ischemia is a lack of ____________ supply and infarction is a lack of _________ supply. (two words separated by one space)
19. The deep fascia of the forearm is called the _______________ fascia.
20. The deep fascia of the arm is called the _______________ fascia.
21. The superficial vein located on the medial aspect of the arm is the _______________ vein.
22. An extension of dense connective tissue from the deep fascia of a limb to the bone is called a _______________.
23. A common site of short-term venous cannulation is the ___________ vein of the upper limb.
24. The radius and ulna are joined by a sheet of dense connective tissue called the _______________ _______________ membrane.
